💻 Software Integration Guide

For Cytotron (India)

1. Identify communication interface (likely RS-232 or Ethernet)
2. Request API/protocol documentation from manufacturer (CARD, Bengaluru)
3. Your software sends frequency/beam commands via socket/Serial
4. Read feedback (phase, amplitude) for PLL auto-tuning

For TTFields Devices (China)

1. Most are closed, fixed-frequency systems – you cannot alter core output
2. Your software acts as a Companion Analytics Tool:
   · Read treatment logs via USB
   · Track patient compliance (wear time)
   · Generate efficacy reports
   · Monitor electrode patch replacement schedules

General Integration Tips

1. Your software's hardware_interface.py currently uses SET_FREQ, READ_PHASE, READ_AMP commands
2. For Cytotron: Map these to the device's native protocol
3. For TTFields: Modify the HAL to read data only (no frequency control)
4. Always test on dummy loads before clinical use

